---------------------------------------------------------------***--------------------------------------------------------------------------
In this problem we will be following the following steps:-

1.We need to take values of two variables as input.
2.Then we will use another variable c to store the value of remainder when a is divided by b;
3.We can now output the value of c.
---------------------------------------------------------------***--------------------------------------------------------------------------

CODE :- 

#include<iostream>
using namespace std;

int main(){
    int a;
    int b;
    int c=a%b;
    cout<<c<<endl;
    return 0;
}

Note :- We can also directly print the value of remainder (no use of c) by just using [ cout<<a%b<<endl ].
